latestPosts.caption:
At least 11 people died and 47+ others were injured as a stampede occurred at Chinnaswamy Stadium in Bengaluru after a large number of people gathered to participate in the RCB victory celebrations. Prime Minister Narendra Modi called the incident “absolutely heartrending” and prayed for the speedy recovery of the injured people. Karnataka chief minister Siddaramaiah held a press conference and announced Rs 10 lakh as compensation to the kin of those deceased. He also ordered a magisterial inquiry into the incident. 
Source: TOI, HT

The sacred Saroop of Sri Guru Granth Sahib Ji, which was struck by bullets during the 1984 Sri Darbar Sahib Incident, has now been respectfully placed for Darshan. This moment holds immense emotional and spiritual significance for the Sikh community around the world.

This bullet-hit Saroop stands as a living testimony to the unshakable resilience of the Sikh spirit and the desecration that took place during the tragic events of June 1984. The damage inflicted on this sacred scripture is not just physical—it reflects a painful chapter in Sikh history that continues to echo through generations.

Today, as the Sangat gathers to offer reverence, this Saroop reminds us of the need to preserve our history, honor the martyrs, and reflect deeply on the sacrifices made in the name of faith and justice. 

Waheguru Ji 🙏🏼
